{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1774358429,"nonce":"swoB3rQ55hXUK4XramUQklQUXjg=","message":"## Run 2: Phase 1 results (WITH gradient fix)\n\nPrevious Run 1 had zero gradients due to model.net vs model.nodes['net'] identity mismatch (bug e08aeb5 in feedbax). All Run 1 models were untrained.\n\n### Training results (all 10k batches, 5 replicates, PAI-ASF, nn_output=1e-5 fixed)\n\n| Condition | Loss change | Endpoint error | Peak speed | Final speed | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| running_cost | 32.3 → 2.9 (-91%) | 0.007 | 3.33 | 0.019 | Excellent |\n| combined | 10.7 → 5.0 (-54%) | 0.15 | 2.06 | 0.29 | Mediocre |\n| softmin | 5.0 → 843 (+16700%) | 2.34 | 2.96 | 2.28 | DIVERGED |\n| default | 14.9 → 885 (+5850%) | 1.53 | 3.82 | 2.49 | DIVERGED |\n\n### SISU-dependent peak velocity (running_cost condition)\n\n| SISU | Peak velocity | Endpoint error |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0.00 | 3.330 ± 0.044 | 0.007 |\n| 0.25 | 3.329 ± 0.040 | 0.006 |\n| 0.50 | 3.327 ± 0.037 | 0.006 |\n| 0.75 | 3.321 ± 0.028 | 0.007 |\n| 1.00 | 3.321 ± 0.027 | 0.008 |\n\nSISU 0→1 peak velocity change: **-0.3%** (no increase)\n\n### Interpretation\n\n1. **running_cost is the only viable loss mode** — softmin and default both diverge, combined partially works\n2. **The running cost produces excellent reaching** — 0.007 endpoint error, clean settling\n3. **SISU has no effect on peak velocity** — the model reaches at the same speed regardless of uncertainty signal\n4. This confirms the analysis: expected-cost training (standard backprop) does not produce the H-infinity velocity signature even with the correct running-cost loss structure\n5. Next: try CVaR or APT training objectives, which shift optimization toward worst-case\n\n### Feedbax bugs found and fixed this session\n- e08aeb5: model.net vs model.nodes['net'] identity mismatch (CRITICAL — zero gradients)\n- a3244be: tree_infer_batch_size fails with StateIndex leaves\n- 0ae27c9: filter_spec_leaves doesn't expand Module-level True to leaves\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}